      "id": 1279,
      "from_id": "cec50b17:0",
      "to_id": "cec50b17:27",
      "content": "Work inside `.synapse/worktrees/developer-0-remove-env-forwarding`. Commit there. Do not push.\n\n**Task:** Remove the `ENV_VARS_TO_FORWARD` feature from `src/spawn.ts`. This feature explicitly forwards ANTHROPIC_* and proxy env vars from the parent process into the worker launcher script. We want to remove it to prevent env vars from leaking across projects when workers are spawned.\n\n**What to do:**\nIn `src/spawn.ts`, find and remove the `ENV_VARS_TO_FORWARD` array and all code that uses it to inject `export VAR=...` lines into the launcher script. The launcher script should only set `SYNAPSE_DB_PATH` (not any ANTHROPIC or proxy vars). Workers will rely on whatever env they inherit naturally from their tmux window.\n\nSpecifically remove:\n- The `ENV_VARS_TO_FORWARD` constant (the array with ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL, etc.)\n- The `.filter()` and `.map()` that turn it into `export` lines\n- The `...envLines` spread in the `writeFileSync` call for the launcher script\n- Any `const envLines = ...` variable\n\nKeep the `SYNAPSE_DB_PATH` export in the launcher — only remove the ANTHROPIC/proxy var forwarding.\n\nAfter editing, run `npm run build` to verify it compiles. Then commit with a clear message.",
